00:10:13,419 --> 00:10:15,490
(They're so cute.)

261
00:10:16,690 --> 00:10:20,289
- Good night.
- Good night.

262
00:10:20,289 --> 00:10:22,129
- Good night.
- Bye.

263
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:25,559
(Coming closer)

264
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:27,600
(Monk Bad Boy wants to film Kian TV.)

265
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,830
Are you filming me?

266
00:10:30,129 --> 00:10:31,899
(Bad Boy TV)

267
00:10:31,899 --> 00:10:34,340
It was a very long day.

268
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:38,009
It's getting more tiring every day.

269
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:40,210
I'm so tired.

270
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:41,649
(Today was especially a long day.)

271
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:47,080
(He woke up in the morning at the campsite
at 4,400m above sea level.)

272
00:10:48,149 --> 00:10:50,120
(He started his day refreshingly
with dry-heaves.)

273
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:53,759
(After spending a short morning
with the other guys, he said goodbye.)

274
00:10:53,759 --> 00:10:55,590
- It's weird to see myself in the video.
- Good luck.

275
00:10:55,590 --> 00:10:56,929
- Bye.
- Good luck.

276
00:10:57,860 --> 00:11:01,269
(The journey by himself began again.)

277
00:11:01,970 --> 00:11:04,799
(Half excited and half scared,
he had mixed feelings.)

278
00:11:05,570 --> 00:11:07,539
(Dry-heaving)

279
00:11:07,539 --> 00:11:09,210
(Dry-heaving again)

280
00:11:09,909 --> 00:11:11,710
He made new friends soon.

281
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:12,710
- Yes.
- This is great.

282
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:13,940
(After traveling a long distance,
he met new people, which wasn't easy.)

283
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:17,049
It all happened in one day.

284
00:11:17,649 --> 00:11:19,049
Why is the day not ending?

285
00:11:19,049 --> 00:11:21,350
(Why is the day not ending?)

286
00:11:21,649 --> 00:11:22,750
(He was extremely busy
in a place isolated from civilization.)

287
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:24,889
Why is the day not ending?

288
00:11:24,889 --> 00:11:26,320
It feels like it's not the same 24 hours.

289
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,360
- I know.
- It's like a dream.

290
00:11:28,059 --> 00:11:29,490
Let's turn off the light.

291
00:11:29,759 --> 00:11:31,429
The light. How there?

292
00:11:31,429 --> 00:11:33,230
"How dare?"
"How dare we keep the light on?"

293
00:11:33,230 --> 00:11:34,529
- "How dare you turn on the light?"
- We can't turn it off?

294
00:11:34,629 --> 00:11:37,370
- No. It goes off at 11 p.m.
- No.

295
00:11:37,539 --> 00:11:39,840
- I see. At 11 p.m.
- Yes. It goes off at 11 p.m.

296
00:11:39,899 --> 00:11:43,370
Hey, it will go off at 10 p.m.

297
00:11:44,179 --> 00:11:45,580
Okay. Let's go to sleep.

298
00:11:46,009 --> 00:11:47,139
Sleep!

299
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,279
Sleep!

300
00:11:48,279 --> 00:11:49,409
(He goes to sleep...)

301
00:11:49,409 --> 00:11:50,509
How cute.

302
00:11:50,879 --> 00:11:51,879
Let's go to sleep.

303
00:11:51,879 --> 00:11:53,080
(with the 7 boy monks
like a happy family.)

304
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:03,090
- It was cold there.
- Was it cold?

305
00:12:03,889 --> 00:12:06,200
(How's his morning in Korzok Village
with the 7 boy monks?)

306
00:12:07,330 --> 00:12:08,700
(The 7 boy monks are all awake.)

307
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:10,299
It got lively when it was time to wake up.

308
00:12:10,769 --> 00:12:12,470
(Where's Kian84?)

309
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:14,039
(Coughing)

310
00:12:14,039 --> 00:12:15,070
Oh, no.

311
00:12:15,470 --> 00:12:16,470
Because it was cold?

312
00:12:17,509 --> 00:12:19,279
(Peeking)

313
00:12:19,679 --> 00:12:21,450
(Half asleep)

314
00:12:22,049 --> 00:12:24,350
Wake up, everyone.

315
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,879
It's the morning roll call.

316
00:12:28,620 --> 00:12:30,789
The boys were well-disciplined.

317
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:34,289
(Kian84 who just woke up
gets up with the boys.)

318
00:12:34,490 --> 00:12:35,659
I'll do it with you.

319
00:12:37,559 --> 00:12:38,759
(Kian84 helps the boys
with disheveled hair.)

320
00:12:38,759 --> 00:12:40,159
Gosh. I should have washed my hair.

321
00:12:41,330 --> 00:12:43,269
(He helps out the eldest boy monk.)

322
00:12:44,399 --> 00:12:47,169
That's right. You have to fold it neatly.
You have to keep the angles sharp.

323
00:12:47,299 --> 00:12:50,039
I think those boys will fit in better
at the military camp than Dex.

324
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:53,679
(He's trying to rest up in a corner.)

325
00:12:54,149 --> 00:12:55,679
Everyone, sit down.

326
00:12:56,850 --> 00:12:57,879
(The 7 boy monks sit nicely in a row.)

327
00:12:57,879 --> 00:12:58,980
Gosh. What's going on?

328
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:02,519
(They start reciting Buddhist scriptures
in the morning.)

329
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:04,159
I see. They do that
as soon as they wake up.

330
00:13:04,820 --> 00:13:06,960
They were reviewing the scriptures...

331
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:10,090
they had learned thus far in the morning.
They chanted in the morning.

332
00:13:11,059 --> 00:13:13,029
(Glancing)

333
00:13:13,860 --> 00:13:15,200
(Approaching)

334
00:13:17,639 --> 00:13:20,909
(He steps back and naturally joins them.)

335
00:13:21,769 --> 00:13:24,139
(What's this?)

336
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:30,279
You can't even read it, though.

337
00:13:30,549 --> 00:13:31,879
- I can't read it at all.
- Right.

338
00:13:32,049 --> 00:13:34,350
Do the boy monks study every single day?

339
00:13:34,350 --> 00:13:36,419
- They do that every morning?
- Yes.

340
00:13:36,419 --> 00:13:38,990
- Gosh. That's amazing.
- They do it to be enlightened.

341
00:13:39,789 --> 00:13:42,860
(Unlike the 7 boy monks who are chanting
at the top of their lungs,)

342
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:49,870
(he's the only one staying quiet.)

343
00:13:50,529 --> 00:13:53,769
(He feels left out for some reason.)

344
00:13:55,740 --> 00:13:58,039
In the morning, they chanted...

345
00:13:58,039 --> 00:14:00,409
the Buddhist scriptures.
I mean they are monks, after all.

346
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:03,509
But I didn't know what they were saying.
I can't read...

347
00:14:03,610 --> 00:14:05,250
the letters at all.

348
00:14:06,419 --> 00:14:09,049
(He unexpectedly comes face-to-face
with the language barrier.)

349
00:14:10,019 --> 00:14:12,690
Where are you, Pani Bottle?

350
00:14:12,690 --> 00:14:15,259
Where are you, Dex?

351
00:14:15,259 --> 00:14:16,559
His eyes are out of focus.

352
00:14:16,860 --> 00:14:20,299
I miss you guys

353
00:14:21,029 --> 00:14:24,169
Where have you gone, leaving me here?

354
00:14:25,639 --> 00:14:29,539
India

355
00:14:29,909 --> 00:14:33,610
India is not easy here

356
00:14:34,139 --> 00:14:35,179
(Zoning out)

357
00:14:37,350 --> 00:14:40,649
(For some reason, he feels empty inside.)

358
00:14:41,389 --> 00:14:45,389
I want to eat kimchi jjigae

359
00:14:45,389 --> 00:14:48,259
- He means it.
- I want to eat jokbal with soju

360
00:14:48,259 --> 00:14:49,990
He's following
his stream of consciousness.

361
00:14:49,990 --> 00:14:51,929
I kept spitting out words
after hearing them chant.

362
00:14:52,330 --> 00:14:54,159
(The 7 boy monks are reciting
the Buddhist scriptures.)

363
00:14:54,159 --> 00:14:57,269
Sashimi with soju

364
00:14:57,330 --> 00:14:59,600
Roe soup with soju

365
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:02,570
If I could go to sleep after a drink

366
00:15:02,570 --> 00:15:06,009
I would have nothing to wish for

367
00:15:06,110 --> 00:15:07,710
(Chuckling)

368
00:15:07,750 --> 00:15:09,950
He's getting close to enlightenment.

369
00:15:11,379 --> 00:15:13,350
(Pulling his sleeves)

370
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:15,220
(Blowing out his nose)

371
00:15:16,190 --> 00:15:17,490
What? On your clothes?

372
00:15:17,490 --> 00:15:20,559
Gosh. Why is my nose so itchy?

373
00:15:21,330 --> 00:15:24,159
The chanting session is quite long.

374
00:15:24,330 --> 00:15:26,899
Gosh. They can stay focused
for a long time.

375
00:15:26,899 --> 00:15:28,200
- They are studying hard.
- Yes.

376
00:15:28,799 --> 00:15:30,169
(Glancing)

377
00:15:30,870 --> 00:15:32,740
(Fidgeting)

378
00:15:33,470 --> 00:15:35,769
(As he observes the 7 boy monks,
chanting the scriptures...)

379
00:15:37,539 --> 00:15:40,139
(You love me, but I'm sorry,
I'm a bad boy)

380
00:15:40,539 --> 00:15:41,809
Is he okay?

381
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,149
He's in trouble now.

382
00:15:46,419 --> 00:15:47,620
That's an unholy song to sing.

383
00:15:47,620 --> 00:15:48,990
He said, "bad boy."

384
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:52,419
Gosh. The boy monk is very surprised.

385
00:15:52,419 --> 00:15:53,460
(Flustered)

386
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:56,889
(He starts singing the next song
without any delay.)

387
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:01,169
(Without knowing why, he starts singing.)

388
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:04,029
He's like, "What's wrong with that uncle?"

389
00:16:04,299 --> 00:16:05,639
(What's going on with him?)

390
00:16:05,970 --> 00:16:07,240
Those boys must be thinking,

391
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:09,840
- "I see. He's praying too."
- Right.

392
00:16:10,269 --> 00:16:12,009
(Their eyes are fixed on him.)

393
00:16:12,009 --> 00:16:14,139
But I think that's very natural.

394
00:16:14,139 --> 00:16:15,950
He can't check his cell phone there.

395
00:16:15,950 --> 00:16:17,080
- Right.
- Yes.

396
00:16:17,919 --> 00:16:20,220
I was talking to myself
and then started singing.

397
00:16:20,549 --> 00:16:23,490
During this process,
I might be enlightened.

398
00:16:23,490 --> 00:16:25,360
I was just following
my stream of consciousness.

399
00:16:25,519 --> 00:16:27,590
- Right. That's all you could do.
- Yes. It's okay as long as he was happy.

400
00:16:27,590 --> 00:16:28,759
(He happily chants his own scriptures.)

401
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:31,360
(They are puzzled by Kian84's chanting.)

402
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:35,200
(Fascinated)

403
00:16:35,899 --> 00:16:38,370
(I'm going to recite
my own Buddhist scriptures.)

404
00:16:39,570 --> 00:16:41,470
(Scriptures84)

405
00:16:41,470 --> 00:16:42,870
- "How disrespectful."
- He looked.

406
00:16:46,340 --> 00:16:48,409
(Hey.)

407
00:16:48,409 --> 00:16:50,149
(Look at him.)

408
00:16:50,309 --> 00:16:51,950
(Tapping)

409
00:16:52,179 --> 00:16:54,389
(Sharing the news to the eldest boy monk)

410
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:56,490
What should I sing next?

411
00:16:56,590 --> 00:16:59,220
What are some scriptures that I know of?

412
00:16:59,220 --> 00:17:00,990
There was a rhythm to this.

413
00:17:01,129 --> 00:17:02,659
You were reciting your own scriptures.

414
00:17:02,659 --> 00:17:05,200
What are some scriptures that I know of?
Let's see.

415
00:17:06,130 --> 00:17:08,970
(He keeps chanting his scriptures.)

416
00:17:10,369 --> 00:17:12,539
(The song she liked)

417
00:17:12,539 --> 00:17:13,539
(Coughing)

418
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,509
(Retching)

419
00:17:16,210 --> 00:17:18,740
(The more he looks at Kian84,
the more intrigued he becomes.)

420
00:17:19,779 --> 00:17:21,349
(Doing the lip trill)

421
00:17:23,849 --> 00:17:25,880
(Scriptures84 starts warming up
his throat in earnest.)

422
00:17:26,049 --> 00:17:28,420
(Humming)

423
00:17:29,349 --> 00:17:30,420
Hello?

424
00:17:31,319 --> 00:17:32,359
Hello?

425
00:17:32,359 --> 00:17:33,920
- What's going on? What was that?
- What is gotten into him?

426
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:35,730
("Lies" by BigBang)

427
00:17:36,230 --> 00:17:37,900
(Oh, my goodness)

428
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:39,299
He sings that all the time.

429
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,930
I wasn't myself.

430
00:17:41,369 --> 00:17:44,329
(I'm so sorry, but I love you,
that was all a lie)

431
00:17:45,740 --> 00:17:47,940
(When the boy monks are chanting
the sacred scriptures,)

432
00:17:48,539 --> 00:17:50,710
(Kian84's scriptures sound unholy
for some reason.)

433
00:17:50,710 --> 00:17:52,279
He's really following
his stream of consciousness.

434
00:17:56,009 --> 00:17:58,180
(As they chant their own scriptures,)

435
00:17:58,450 --> 00:18:00,019
(Kian84's scriptures...)

436
00:18:00,019 --> 00:18:01,720
(are accompanied by
the eldest boy monk's scriptures.)

437
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:04,460
(You still don't know)

438
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,990
(As Kian84 sings passionately
with all of his heart,)

439
00:18:07,390 --> 00:18:09,630
(the 7 boy monks harmonize with him.)

440
00:18:10,029 --> 00:18:12,930
(The man who has you)

441
00:18:13,430 --> 00:18:16,269
(They are reaching the climax.)

442
00:18:17,029 --> 00:18:19,200
(Please)

443
00:18:19,940 --> 00:18:25,380
(Don't leave me)

444
00:18:25,609 --> 00:18:28,710
(The scripture orchestra
by Scriptures84 and the 7 boy monks)

445
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:30,410
Did it last about 30 minutes?

446
00:18:30,410 --> 00:18:31,980
- It lasted an hour.
- I see.

447
00:18:31,980 --> 00:18:33,480
- It's finally over.
- Gosh.

448
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:35,119
Gosh, they gave it their all.

449
00:18:35,819 --> 00:18:38,119
But it did clear up my head.

450
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:40,589
- Have breakfast.
- Breakfast.

451
00:18:40,589 --> 00:18:41,630
Come here.

452
00:18:42,329 --> 00:18:44,460
They're carefully wrapping the books
with the cloth.

453
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,029
Let's wrap it up.

454
00:18:46,029 --> 00:18:47,059
(Right here.)

455
00:18:47,599 --> 00:18:49,500
(He gets Kian84's help
to put away the book.)

456
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,569
(Feeling proud)

457
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,109
(He quickly puts on his bag.)

458
00:18:55,109 --> 00:18:57,309
Let's go and eat.

459
00:18:58,410 --> 00:19:00,480
- Do you still have the bag?
- Of course.

460
00:19:02,579 --> 00:19:03,950
I see. Breakfast.

461
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:06,519
(Lining up)

462
00:19:07,049 --> 00:19:08,450
We're getting bread for breakfast.

463
00:19:09,490 --> 00:19:10,549
(Bread with strawberry jam and butter)

464
00:19:10,549 --> 00:19:11,859
- It smells nice.
- Gosh, that looks good.

465
00:19:11,859 --> 00:19:14,089
- It looks like a real breakfast.
- It's an English breakfast.

466
00:19:14,089 --> 00:19:15,730
- Nice.
- That was really good.

467
00:19:15,730 --> 00:19:16,789
That does look good.

468
00:19:16,789 --> 00:19:18,500
- Of course, it's bound to taste good.
- Yes.

469
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:19,500
(Spreading the strawberry jam generously)

470
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:22,269
- Gosh. The butter too.
- The bread looks tasty.

471
00:19:22,369 --> 00:19:24,170
At the bootcamp in Nonsan,
you can't get refills.

472
00:19:24,299 --> 00:19:25,539
- But there...
- Can you get refills?

473
00:19:25,599 --> 00:19:28,339
- You can get the jam 2 or 3 more times.
- That must have been good.

474
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:30,109
That small boy is having two.

475
00:19:30,140 --> 00:19:31,940
(Two pieces of bread)

476
00:19:32,380 --> 00:19:34,849
(They don't forget to pray
before the meal.)

477
00:19:35,309 --> 00:19:37,049
(Mumbling something
to the best of his ability)

478
00:19:37,109 --> 00:19:39,019
You can sort of copy them now.

479
00:19:39,819 --> 00:19:42,220
(Everyone is praying
while holding the bread with one hand.)

480
00:19:42,490 --> 00:19:45,190
(He glances around and does the same.)

481
00:19:48,259 --> 00:19:49,490
Thank you for the food.

482
00:19:49,990 --> 00:19:51,529
Gosh, that looks good.

483
00:19:52,359 --> 00:19:53,829
- Gosh. It must be good.
- Goodness.

484
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,940
That looks like a pastry.

485
00:19:57,940 --> 00:20:00,299
- It must be crunchy.
- It looks tasty.

486
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:03,309
(Munching)

487
00:20:04,140 --> 00:20:06,339
(Monk Saliva is eating the food
with gusto.)

488
00:20:06,940 --> 00:20:08,849
(But this guy is enjoying the food
more than Monk Saliva.)

489
00:20:08,849 --> 00:20:10,109
You look starved.

490
00:20:12,150 --> 00:20:13,319
He wiped his nose on that sleeve.

491
00:20:13,319 --> 00:20:14,420
Right. It's sweet and salty.

492
00:20:15,650 --> 00:20:17,789
Ki, is the bread very delicious?

493
00:20:18,059 --> 00:20:19,789
- Delicious.
- Do you like it?

494
00:20:19,789 --> 00:20:21,829
- Yes.
- Okay.

495
00:20:22,329 --> 00:20:24,430
When are they going to school?

496
00:20:24,430 --> 00:20:26,230
- Nine o'clock.
- Nine o'clock.

497
00:20:26,460 --> 00:20:28,269
Does a monk teach them?

498
00:20:29,630 --> 00:20:31,740
- Science.
- Science.

499
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,000
What's math in English?

500
00:20:34,369 --> 00:20:36,210
- What's math in English?
- Math.

501
00:20:36,269 --> 00:20:39,009
- Mathematics.
- He can understand Korean.

502
00:20:39,009 --> 00:20:41,450
- Hindi. English.
- Hindi. Yes.

503
00:20:41,450 --> 00:20:43,150
- Bhoti.
- Bhoti.

504
00:20:43,410 --> 00:20:45,549
- You teach them?
- Five subjects.

505
00:20:45,549 --> 00:20:46,650
- I teach.
- Gosh.

506
00:20:46,650 --> 00:20:48,220
It turns out he also teaches them.

507
00:20:48,220 --> 00:20:50,119
- He's a teacher too.
- I see.

508
00:20:50,119 --> 00:20:52,359
In elementary school,
our homeroom teacher taught...

509
00:20:52,359 --> 00:20:53,990
- every subject.
- They taught us everything.

510
00:20:53,990 --> 00:20:56,490
Then do you also teach them art?

511
00:20:56,829 --> 00:20:59,799
I teach them everything I know.

512
00:21:02,029 --> 00:21:03,769
(He shoves
in the last piece of his bread.)

513
00:21:04,069 --> 00:21:05,539
He's cleaning up too.

514
00:21:08,009 --> 00:21:09,440
(Staring)

515
00:21:10,210 --> 00:21:11,309
