01:10:05,569 --> 01:10:07,140
There's one of each size.

1835
01:10:07,680 --> 01:10:08,680
(What could it be?)

1836
01:10:08,680 --> 01:10:10,210
- They're going to love it.
- Here.

1837
01:10:11,210 --> 01:10:12,350
Karzam.

1838
01:10:12,510 --> 01:10:13,710
Skarzan.

1839
01:10:13,710 --> 01:10:15,180
(He called on Jigmed Skarzan,
Monk Nightmare.)

1840
01:10:15,779 --> 01:10:17,279
I'll do it.

1841
01:10:18,289 --> 01:10:21,689
Deshap?

1842
01:10:21,689 --> 01:10:23,560
(Tiring Sandup, Monk Saliva)

1843
01:10:23,560 --> 01:10:24,930
- Say, "Thank you."
- Thank you.

1844
01:10:24,930 --> 01:10:27,229
(He understood through amazing telepathy
and received his jacket.)

1845
01:10:27,960 --> 01:10:29,729
Yisip. Nawang.

1846
01:10:30,260 --> 01:10:31,430
Jimel Sabel.

1847
01:10:31,430 --> 01:10:32,500
Dorji.

1848
01:10:33,270 --> 01:10:35,439
(Everyone got their jacket.)

1849
01:10:36,140 --> 01:10:37,970
- Who is this for?
- There's no name.

1850
01:10:39,609 --> 01:10:42,140
It seems like
Crying Monk didn't get anything.

1851
01:10:42,140 --> 01:10:43,779
Oh, no.

1852
01:10:43,779 --> 01:10:44,850
He might cry.

1853
01:10:44,850 --> 01:10:46,010
- No name.
- No.

1854
01:10:46,010 --> 01:10:47,109
- Where's Crying Monk's?
- Quickly.

1855
01:10:47,109 --> 01:10:49,750
- He's crying again.
- Jigmed Lachok.

1856
01:10:49,949 --> 01:10:51,020
(He's starting to cry.)

1857
01:10:51,020 --> 01:10:53,220
No. Before he starts to cry...

1858
01:10:53,420 --> 01:10:55,289
- He has to get one before he cries.
- We should have given him his first.

1859
01:10:55,289 --> 01:10:56,460
No, quickly.

1860
01:10:56,789 --> 01:10:58,060
(He's starting to cry.)

1861
01:10:58,060 --> 01:10:59,260
Jigmed Lachok.

1862
01:11:00,359 --> 01:11:01,359
(Fortunately, he received his gift
before he turned on the waterworks.)

1863
01:11:01,359 --> 01:11:03,600
- What a relief.
- What a relief.

1864
01:11:03,600 --> 01:11:06,729
The corners of his mouth were wobbling.

1865
01:11:06,729 --> 01:11:08,140
That would be a problem.

1866
01:11:08,800 --> 01:11:09,899
(The gifts are endless as if there's
a vase of inexhaustible treasures.)

1867
01:11:09,899 --> 01:11:12,670
Here you go. These are from me.

1868
01:11:13,539 --> 01:11:15,239
(What's this?)

1869
01:11:15,239 --> 01:11:16,840
(Gosh, it's a jacket.)

1870
01:11:17,649 --> 01:11:18,710
Take a hat too.

1871
01:11:19,579 --> 01:11:20,979
- Take a hat.
- You're like Santa Claus.

1872
01:11:20,979 --> 01:11:22,250
- Really.
- Right.

1873
01:11:22,819 --> 01:11:24,250
Yes, try it on.

1874
01:11:24,250 --> 01:11:25,949
(Let's try on our new clothes.)

1875
01:11:26,789 --> 01:11:28,659
Monk Saliva, where's your jacket?

1876
01:11:30,489 --> 01:11:31,930
They're all matching in red.

1877
01:11:32,859 --> 01:11:35,159
The unique color of Tibetan Buddhism...

1878
01:11:35,159 --> 01:11:36,260
is red.

1879
01:11:37,329 --> 01:11:39,869
(Kian84 put Monk Saliva's sweater on him.)

1880
01:11:40,800 --> 01:11:41,840
(And he helped him with his pants too.)

1881
01:11:41,840 --> 01:11:42,899
Okay?

1882
01:11:43,869 --> 01:11:46,539
(The pants almost reach his neck.)

1883
01:11:47,039 --> 01:11:48,140
Are they too long?

1884
01:11:48,739 --> 01:11:49,779
You'll grow into it soon.

1885
01:11:51,010 --> 01:11:53,350
Gosh, you look nice.

1886
01:11:53,880 --> 01:11:56,180
You'll charm everyone in Ladakh.

1887
01:11:56,180 --> 01:11:57,520
(Monk Fashion will blow Ladakh away.)

1888
01:11:57,689 --> 01:12:00,220
I dressed Monk Saliva.

1889
01:12:00,220 --> 01:12:02,489
He could have refused to wear them,

1890
01:12:02,489 --> 01:12:04,020
but he happily did,
and I'm thankful for that.

1891
01:12:04,430 --> 01:12:07,029
Actually, the clothes were
all slightly different.

1892
01:12:07,460 --> 01:12:09,100
I thought they would get into an argument
to take each other's clothes,

1893
01:12:09,100 --> 01:12:10,529
but there wasn't anything
like that at all.

1894
01:12:10,600 --> 01:12:12,699
It was nice, things like that.

1895
01:12:12,699 --> 01:12:15,869
I was a bit sad
that was all I could do for them.

1896
01:12:15,970 --> 01:12:18,409
They might make "Kian84 Day"
for what you did.

1897
01:12:18,510 --> 01:12:19,970
Kian84 Day might really be a thing.

1898
01:12:19,970 --> 01:12:22,079
They might make Kian84 Day.

1899
01:12:22,079 --> 01:12:24,479
They'll think of Kian84 as they recite
Buddhist scriptures in the morning.

1900
01:12:24,479 --> 01:12:26,279
Like how we celebrate May 5.

1901
01:12:26,279 --> 01:12:27,949
You're like Bang Jeong Hwan.

1902
01:12:28,079 --> 01:12:29,220
(The Bang Jeong Hwan of Ladakh)

1903
01:12:29,220 --> 01:12:30,619
- Bang Jeong Hwan?
- Bang Jeong Hwan.

1904
01:12:31,449 --> 01:12:33,149
Okay.

1905
01:12:34,020 --> 01:12:35,359
Gather around.

1906
01:12:36,189 --> 01:12:37,289
Gather around.

1907
01:12:37,289 --> 01:12:38,890
- Move closer together.
- They're adorable.

1908
01:12:38,890 --> 01:12:41,199
- They're so cute.
- Okay.

1909
01:12:41,800 --> 01:12:42,800
Okay.

1910
01:12:43,430 --> 01:12:44,529
Go.

1911
01:12:44,529 --> 01:12:45,529
(This moment will one day fade away.)

1912
01:12:45,529 --> 01:12:48,039
Look. You're hiding him a little.

1913
01:12:48,100 --> 01:12:49,399
Come here, Crying Monk.

1914
01:12:49,399 --> 01:12:50,500
(Hopefully, this picture will help them
hold onto it for a long time.)

1915
01:12:50,500 --> 01:12:51,770
All right.

1916
01:12:52,010 --> 01:12:54,409
One, two, three.

1917
01:12:54,409 --> 01:12:55,409
Smile.

1918
01:12:56,840 --> 01:12:58,310
They're wearing matching hats.

1919
01:12:58,510 --> 01:12:59,609
Okay.

1920
01:13:01,119 --> 01:13:02,180
Thank you.

1921
01:13:02,180 --> 01:13:03,520
(Did the picture turn out nice?)

1922
01:13:03,520 --> 01:13:04,520
Wait.

1923
01:13:04,520 --> 01:13:06,050
Why is it so dark?

1924
01:13:08,319 --> 01:13:10,359
Those kids are always smiling.

1925
01:13:10,359 --> 01:13:11,659
They always have smiles on their faces.

1926
01:13:12,060 --> 01:13:14,260
(Precious)

1927
01:13:15,600 --> 01:13:18,000
This time with Kian84.

1928
01:13:18,000 --> 01:13:19,000
(This time with Kian84.)

1929
01:13:19,000 --> 01:13:20,729
(No problem.)

1930
01:13:21,239 --> 01:13:23,800
(Having been a 1-day teacher
of the 7 boy monks,)

1931
01:13:24,739 --> 01:13:27,510
(a friend, and Santa Claus...)

1932
01:13:27,510 --> 01:13:29,439
- Gosh.
- Gosh.

1933
01:13:29,439 --> 01:13:30,680
(is a precious memory.)

1934
01:13:30,680 --> 01:13:32,680
"We're a family."
It's like a family picture.

1935
01:13:34,050 --> 01:13:35,880
This is so nice to watch,

1936
01:13:35,880 --> 01:13:38,390
but as nice as it is, saying goodbye...

1937
01:13:39,020 --> 01:13:40,420
will be extremely sad.

1938
01:13:42,619 --> 01:13:43,890
Is it the last night already?

1939
01:13:43,890 --> 01:13:45,829
Yes, it's his last night here.

1940
01:13:46,689 --> 01:13:48,229
Don't you miss your moms?

1941
01:13:49,130 --> 01:13:51,470
When was the last time you saw your mom?

1942
01:13:51,470 --> 01:13:53,670
- One month.
- One month?

1943
01:13:54,130 --> 01:13:58,439
Then tell me how long you have been here.

1944
01:13:59,409 --> 01:14:00,770
Who has been here the longest?

1945
01:14:00,770 --> 01:14:02,140
I've been here for two years.

1946
01:14:02,140 --> 01:14:03,140
How long?

1947
01:14:03,279 --> 01:14:04,310
Two years?

1948
01:14:04,880 --> 01:14:07,920
How long have you been here, Monk Saliva?

1949
01:14:09,180 --> 01:14:10,920
- You've been here a month?
- Goodness.

1950
01:14:10,920 --> 01:14:12,850
- You've been here a month?
- He must miss his mom.

1951
01:14:12,850 --> 01:14:15,159
Goodness, you're strong.

1952
01:14:15,159 --> 01:14:16,189
(He's proud of him.)

1953
01:14:16,189 --> 01:14:19,029
Did you all come here
because you want to become monks?

1954
01:14:19,159 --> 01:14:20,659
- Yes.
- Yes.

1955
01:14:20,659 --> 01:14:21,699
- Really?
- Yes.

1956
01:14:21,699 --> 01:14:22,800
Really!

1957
01:14:22,930 --> 01:14:25,930
Even though monks can't eat meat...

1958
01:14:26,029 --> 01:14:29,239
or get married in the future?

1959
01:14:29,239 --> 01:14:30,800
I still want to be one.

1960
01:14:31,210 --> 01:14:33,539
Do you think I'm married or not married?

1961
01:14:33,539 --> 01:14:35,010
- Not married.
- Not married.

1962
01:14:36,310 --> 01:14:38,109
I guess they smelled singlehood on you.

1963
01:14:38,109 --> 01:14:39,710
Maybe I smell like an old bachelor.

1964
01:14:40,010 --> 01:14:41,050
You're right.

1965
01:14:41,449 --> 01:14:43,250
I'm not married.

1966
01:14:43,250 --> 01:14:45,850
How long are you all going to stay here?

1967
01:14:45,850 --> 01:14:47,520
Wouldn't it be nice to go downtown...

1968
01:14:47,520 --> 01:14:51,060
and see the city and be outside?

1969
01:14:51,260 --> 01:14:53,029
I'm going to be here for a long time.

1970
01:14:53,029 --> 01:14:54,090
Really?

1971
01:14:54,189 --> 01:14:56,100
They really have no greed.

1972
01:14:56,100 --> 01:14:57,329
They're so pure.

1973
01:14:57,329 --> 01:14:59,170
They might not think it's good
to go out the way we do.

1974
01:14:59,170 --> 01:15:00,300
Right.

1975
01:15:00,630 --> 01:15:02,439
What do you think happiness is?

1976
01:15:02,899 --> 01:15:03,939
Are you happy?

1977
01:15:04,140 --> 01:15:05,739
Is living here happiness for you?

1978
01:15:05,810 --> 01:15:07,880
Becoming a monk is happiness.

1979
01:15:07,880 --> 01:15:10,739
Monks don't have to herd flocks of sheep,

1980
01:15:10,739 --> 01:15:12,909
and they don't eat meat.

1981
01:15:12,909 --> 01:15:14,550
You're happy about not eating meat?

1982
01:15:14,649 --> 01:15:16,550
Don't you know
how delicious fried chicken is?

1983
01:15:16,619 --> 01:15:17,890
Why did you...

1984
01:15:19,250 --> 01:15:21,119
You enticed them a whole lot.

1985
01:15:21,319 --> 01:15:23,720
Yak steak?

1986
01:15:24,060 --> 01:15:25,090
They're very delicious.

1987
01:15:25,090 --> 01:15:27,430
- How disrespectful.
- How disrespectful.

1988
01:15:27,760 --> 01:15:29,060
No?

1989
01:15:29,060 --> 01:15:30,859
- No.
- No?

1990
01:15:30,859 --> 01:15:32,000
Really?

1991
01:15:32,270 --> 01:15:34,739
But you seemed the happiest
when you were playing cricket.

1992
01:15:34,739 --> 01:15:35,770
Look.

1993
01:15:35,770 --> 01:15:38,909
Would you rather be
a professional cricket player or a monk?

1994
01:15:38,970 --> 01:15:40,810
- Be a monk.
- Be a monk.

1995
01:15:40,810 --> 01:15:42,609
- They're resolute.
- Gosh, really?

1996
01:15:43,479 --> 01:15:45,510
Then what about the eldest?
What do you think is happiness?

1997
01:15:45,880 --> 01:15:48,949
Living here is nice,

1998
01:15:48,949 --> 01:15:52,149
and I was happy while playing
the Korean games today too.

1999
01:15:52,489 --> 01:15:56,020
If you're 18,
you're going through puberty.

2000
01:15:56,020 --> 01:15:59,329
Since you're going through puberty,
don't you want to make a girlfriend?

2001
01:15:59,430 --> 01:16:02,430
We want to become monks.
We don't think about anything else.

2002
01:16:02,529 --> 01:16:04,300
You're not interested in girls?

2003
01:16:04,300 --> 01:16:05,329
Really?

2004
01:16:06,329 --> 01:16:07,829
(He can't believe it.)

2005
01:16:08,170 --> 01:16:09,840
Maybe you're the one who's too tainted.

2006
01:16:10,239 --> 01:16:12,369
You're having a hard time
accepting these kids' innocence.

2007
01:16:12,369 --> 01:16:14,069
Well, it's because I'm so curious.

2008
01:16:14,069 --> 01:16:15,109
Right.

2009
01:16:15,409 --> 01:16:18,510
It seems like you've already
reached enlightenment at 18.

2010
01:16:18,510 --> 01:16:20,050
(You must've reached enlightenment
at 18 years of age.)

2011
01:16:20,279 --> 01:16:22,380
I feel as if I've opened Pandora's box.

2012
01:16:22,720 --> 01:16:24,920
I already know about the good things...

2013
01:16:24,920 --> 01:16:26,250
and the delicious things in the world.

2014
01:16:26,689 --> 01:16:29,189
So, to be honest,
I can't live like a monk.

2015
01:16:29,890 --> 01:16:33,060
They haven't opened Pandora's box yet.

2016
01:16:33,060 --> 01:16:35,060
Maybe that's why those kids are happier.

2017
01:16:35,430 --> 01:16:37,000
That's what I think.

2018
01:16:39,100 --> 01:16:41,029
Study hard to be a monk.

2019
01:16:41,270 --> 01:16:44,569
We all live to be happy.

2020
01:16:44,569 --> 01:16:46,770
I think you and I are the same
in that sense.

2021
01:16:46,770 --> 01:16:48,409
And it feels like
I'm also training myself spiritually.

2022
01:16:48,409 --> 01:16:49,880
Our ways are different,

2023
01:16:49,880 --> 01:16:53,079
but I think we all keep studying ways...

2024
01:16:53,079 --> 01:16:56,079
to be happy in life.

2025
01:16:57,380 --> 01:16:59,989
Is there anything you want to ask me
for the last time?

2026
01:17:01,289 --> 01:17:04,520
I want to come with you.

2027
01:17:04,520 --> 01:17:06,289
(Hiding under the blanket)

2028
01:17:08,329 --> 01:17:10,000
- Gosh.
- He must have enjoyed his time with you.

2029
01:17:10,130 --> 01:17:12,199
Right. Think of how memorable...

2030
01:17:12,970 --> 01:17:14,369
those two days must have been.

2031
01:17:15,699 --> 01:17:18,010
He says he's going with you
when you leave.

2032
01:17:20,810 --> 01:17:23,210
Do you want me to be your dad?
Do you want to be my son?

2033
01:17:24,439 --> 01:17:25,609
Do you want to be my son?

2034
01:17:25,949 --> 01:17:27,909
- Yes.
- Yes?

2035
01:17:27,909 --> 01:17:30,180
You must have felt so emotional.

2036
01:17:31,789 --> 01:17:34,220
Say, "Dad."

2037
01:17:34,819 --> 01:17:36,260
- Dad.
- Dad.

2038
01:17:36,260 --> 01:17:37,789
- Dad.
- That's right.

2039
01:17:38,859 --> 01:17:40,229
You are my sons.

2040
01:17:40,229 --> 01:17:42,329
(You are my sons.)

2041
01:17:42,600 --> 01:17:43,829
Say, "Dad."

2042
01:17:45,899 --> 01:17:48,039
I couldn't help but chuckle
when I heard them say that.

2043
01:17:48,039 --> 01:17:49,140
"Say, 'Dad.'"

2044
01:17:49,199 --> 01:17:50,300
"Dad!"

2045
01:17:50,470 --> 01:17:54,670
(Hearing them say "Dad"
makes him laugh with joy.)

2046
01:17:55,239 --> 01:18:00,050
(When they first met each other,
it was very awkward.)

2047
01:18:01,350 --> 01:18:04,020
(Their innocence found each other,)

2048
01:18:04,020 --> 01:18:07,689
(and their walls crumbled down soon.)

2049
01:18:08,760 --> 01:18:13,689
(They made memories together
beyond borders and generations.)

2050
01:18:14,930 --> 01:18:16,199
I always think about...

2051
01:18:16,199 --> 01:18:18,229
what the best way to live is.

2052
01:18:18,670 --> 01:18:20,430
The conclusion I've drawn is...

2053
01:18:20,670 --> 01:18:23,000
that the best way is to live happily.

2054
01:18:23,000 --> 01:18:25,069
("Since we were born into this life,
let's live happily.")

2055
01:18:25,470 --> 01:18:29,010
Whatever they do, I hope they're happy.

2056
01:18:29,880 --> 01:18:32,649
The enlightenment
they're training to reach...

2057
01:18:32,649 --> 01:18:36,449
I hope they become good monks
who reach enlightenment.

2058
01:18:36,449 --> 01:18:37,520
(He wholeheartedly wishes for
the 7 boy monks to be happy.)

2059
01:18:37,920 --> 01:18:39,619
I want to cheer for them.

2060
01:18:39,619 --> 01:18:41,659
("I want to cheer for them
with all my heart.")

2061
01:18:42,260 --> 01:18:43,720
(I had a good time today.)

2062
01:18:44,689 --> 01:18:46,890
Visit us again. Let's have fun.

2063
01:18:47,630 --> 01:18:49,600
Kim, let's hang out when you visit again.

2064
01:18:50,600 --> 01:18:51,729
- He's cute.
- He's cute.

2065
01:18:52,069 --> 01:18:54,500
- I want to play with Kim more.
- I want to play with Kim more.

2066
01:18:59,510 --> 01:19:01,909
- You should write a video letter to them.
- Yes.

2067
01:19:02,010 --> 01:19:03,039
Why would I?

2068
01:19:03,039 --> 01:19:04,210
- They might watch it.
- Give it a try.

2069
01:19:04,210 --> 01:19:06,250
Why? After asking them to call you Dad?

2070
01:19:06,250 --> 01:19:07,310
He's touched.

2071
01:19:07,310 --> 01:19:10,020
They must be looking for you
and saying, "Dad."

2072
01:19:10,020 --> 01:19:11,350
They have fathers at home.

2073
01:19:11,350 --> 01:19:12,520
- You told them to call you Dad.
- They have real fathers.

2074
01:19:12,520 --> 01:19:13,920
- I'm not their father.
- You're their Korean dad.

2075
01:19:13,920 --> 01:19:15,619
- You're their Korean dad.
- Yes.

2076
01:19:15,619 --> 01:19:17,189
- Their second dad.
- Yes.

2077
01:19:17,689 --> 01:19:18,789
Hi, kids.

2078
01:19:18,789 --> 01:19:21,899
You don't have smartphones there.

2079
01:19:21,899 --> 01:19:23,500
So I'm not sure if you'll watch this,

2080
01:19:24,729 --> 01:19:27,470
but I'm cheering for you, seven monks.

2081
01:19:27,470 --> 01:19:29,270
Please stay healthy,

2082
01:19:31,270 --> 01:19:34,010
and I wish you happiness in life.

2083
01:19:34,010 --> 01:19:35,109
Thank you.

2084
01:19:38,880 --> 01:19:41,380
Okay. Let's go to bed.
I'm sorry. It's late.

2085
01:19:41,550 --> 01:19:43,350
You should go to bed.

2086
01:19:43,350 --> 01:19:44,989
- They must be sad.
- Let's sleep.

2087
01:19:44,989 --> 01:19:46,090
Hey, come.

2088
01:19:46,619 --> 01:19:47,649
Come.

2089
01:19:48,460 --> 01:19:49,659
Come here.

2090
01:19:49,659 --> 01:19:51,119
(Kim who is exhausted
from taking care of the kids all day...)

2091
01:19:52,460 --> 01:19:56,600
(and the mischievous 7 boy monks
get under the blanket.)

2092
01:19:56,600 --> 01:20:00,630
So, I had to leave
before they woke up the next morning.

2093
01:20:00,829 --> 01:20:02,739
So it was the last moment.

2094
01:20:02,739 --> 01:20:04,770
- It was the very last moment.
- That's why I talked with them.

2095
01:20:05,770 --> 01:20:06,810
Good night.

2096
01:20:07,569 --> 01:20:08,609
Good night.

2097
01:20:10,140 --> 01:20:11,140
Good night.

2098
01:20:11,140 --> 01:20:14,449
(They try to sleep,
leaning against one another's warmth.)

2099
01:20:15,250 --> 01:20:16,649
(His last night in India is deepening.)

2100
01:20:16,649 --> 01:20:17,750
It's the last night.

2101
01:20:18,720 --> 01:20:19,819
It's farewell.

2102
01:20:23,090 --> 01:20:25,890
(Rustling)

2103
01:20:26,560 --> 01:20:30,260
(The dawn has come.)

2104
01:20:30,260 --> 01:20:32,829
Even before the sun rose, he came outside.

2105
01:20:33,430 --> 01:20:35,399
(Kim leaves before the dawn breaks.)

2106
01:20:38,340 --> 01:20:40,270
It looks like he's running away
under the cover of darkness.

2107
01:20:40,270 --> 01:20:42,010
Like he has never seen the sun before.

2108
01:20:42,310 --> 01:20:43,609
How disrespectful.

2109
01:20:43,609 --> 01:20:45,279
You ruined my beautiful picture.

2110
01:20:45,750 --> 01:20:47,380
(He's moving with a tired look,
which shows how exhausting it was...)

2111
01:20:47,380 --> 01:20:48,550
(to take care of the kids.)

2112
01:20:48,649 --> 01:20:50,779
Gosh. I feel like I'm going to die.

2113
01:20:51,020 --> 01:20:53,020
He must've been in a very bad condition.

2114
01:20:55,119 --> 01:20:56,119
- Oh, my.
- Gosh.

2115
01:20:56,119 --> 01:20:57,819
(Monk Saliva followed him out
as he heard Kim leaving.)

2116
01:20:57,819 --> 01:20:58,859
Oh, my.

2117
01:20:58,859 --> 01:21:00,760
(I heard something.)

2118
01:21:01,430 --> 01:21:03,260
He ran without shoes on.

2119
01:21:03,659 --> 01:21:05,569
(Dad!)

2120
01:21:06,069 --> 01:21:09,770
(Monk Saliva wasn't shy
around Kim at all.)

2121
01:21:10,670 --> 01:21:14,939
(It was a short time,
but the two got very close.)

2122
01:21:14,939 --> 01:21:15,979
Oh, gosh.

2123
01:21:16,210 --> 01:21:17,680
(They are running toward each other.)

2124
01:21:17,680 --> 01:21:19,109
He came out to say goodbye.

2125
01:21:19,449 --> 01:21:20,649
I grew attached to him.

2126
01:21:21,279 --> 01:21:22,319
Bye.

2127
01:21:22,579 --> 01:21:24,850
- Oh, my. Look at his small hands.
- You're sleepy, aren't you?

2128
01:21:25,149 --> 01:21:26,420
Hurry up, and go back to bed.

2129
01:21:26,420 --> 01:21:28,020
Take care. Okay?

2130
01:21:30,819 --> 01:21:32,329
- Sleep more.
- He must've been tired.

2131
01:21:32,329 --> 01:21:34,329
He kept waking up.

2132
01:21:34,489 --> 01:21:36,060
Bye. Go back to bed.

2133
01:21:36,060 --> 01:21:40,430
(He said farewell with regrets.)

2134
01:21:42,300 --> 01:21:44,300
His feet must've felt so heavy.

2135
01:21:47,670 --> 01:21:52,550
(He stopped by Tso Moriri Lake
before leaving.)

2136
01:21:54,010 --> 01:21:55,050
It's finally...

2137
01:21:55,720 --> 01:21:57,220
the last day in India.

2138
01:21:57,220 --> 01:21:58,390
I'm going back.

2139
01:21:59,090 --> 01:22:01,449
I'm going to see the sunrise
one last time...

2140
01:22:02,560 --> 01:22:03,720
before I go.

2141
01:22:04,920 --> 01:22:07,090
I wanted to see the sunrise
one last time...

2142
01:22:08,460 --> 01:22:11,800
and organize my thoughts. So I went there.

2143
01:22:14,100 --> 01:22:19,239
(He's slowly looking around the scenery
as he's sad to leave.)

2144
01:22:21,039 --> 01:22:24,810
A ray of sunlight is coming down gently.

2145
01:22:24,810 --> 01:22:26,680
(A ray of sunlight is coming down slowly
at the perfect timing.)

2146
01:22:27,310 --> 01:22:28,680
It's rising.

2147
01:22:29,479 --> 01:22:30,680
(Excited)

2148
01:22:30,680 --> 01:22:31,750
It's rising.

2149
01:22:32,989 --> 01:22:34,189
The sun has risen.

2150
01:22:34,189 --> 01:22:37,289
(The sun has risen.)

2151
01:22:37,289 --> 01:22:38,760
I got goosebumps.

2152
01:22:38,930 --> 01:22:42,300
In season one, the sun set at the end.

2153
01:22:42,600 --> 01:22:44,500
But season two ended with the sunrise.

2154
01:22:44,500 --> 01:22:47,600
It feels weird.

2155
01:22:47,600 --> 01:22:49,770
It's Kian84's new beginning.

2156
01:22:49,770 --> 01:22:53,810
And it's also another great start
for our show.

2157
01:22:53,810 --> 01:22:55,779
It's the beginning for all of us.

2158
01:22:56,409 --> 01:22:58,909
It's something I always see,
but I'm so happy to see it.

2159
01:22:59,609 --> 01:23:01,050
It looks wonderful.

2160
01:23:02,550 --> 01:23:03,649
Can you see it?

2161
01:23:04,720 --> 01:23:06,250
It's strangely touching.

2162
01:23:10,720 --> 01:23:13,390
(Kian84's dream country to travel to)

2163
01:23:13,390 --> 01:23:14,890
(India)

2164
01:23:15,529 --> 01:23:18,600
(He went on a second trip
after a long time.)

2165
01:23:19,229 --> 01:23:22,270
(The unfamiliar sights...)

2166
01:23:22,270 --> 01:23:25,439
(made him flustered for a moment,)

2167
01:23:26,109 --> 01:23:29,340
(but he accepted dynamic India
with his entire body.)

2168
01:23:29,340 --> 01:23:31,279
So many things happened.

2169
01:23:33,350 --> 01:23:35,420
(India84 became one with India like that.)

2170
01:23:35,420 --> 01:23:36,819
I can't believe it,
even though I'm watching it.

2171
01:23:36,819 --> 01:23:38,319
It was on my bucket list.

2172
01:23:38,319 --> 01:23:41,520
(He took out his dreams on his bucket list
1 by 1 in the dream country.)

2173
01:23:42,359 --> 01:23:46,229
(He put down everything
at the crematorium.)

2174
01:23:46,729 --> 01:23:51,399
(He enjoyed a wedding
more than the locals themselves.)

2175
01:23:52,000 --> 01:23:54,869
(He could see different worlds
in every compartment in a train in India.)

2176
01:23:55,699 --> 01:24:01,140
(Wherever he went,
unexpected things happened.)

2177
01:24:01,979 --> 01:24:05,079
("Traveling is a magical moment where
you can have unexpected experiences.")

2178
01:24:05,550 --> 01:24:09,579
(He fully enjoyed the trip.)

2179
01:24:10,649 --> 01:24:13,319
(His special friends...)

2180
01:24:13,319 --> 01:24:16,520
(made all of these possible.)

2181
01:24:16,819 --> 01:24:18,859
It feels like I watched a youth drama.

2182
01:24:18,859 --> 01:24:19,890
(Laughing and cheering together)

2183
01:24:20,359 --> 01:24:23,260
(I'm so lucky to have met you guys.)

2184
01:24:24,159 --> 01:24:28,199
(There were other friends who stayed
with him throughout the journey.)

2185
01:24:28,500 --> 01:24:30,699
It felt like I was traveling with them
for ten weeks.

2186
01:24:30,699 --> 01:24:33,109
I don't think even a movie
can be made like this.

2187
01:24:33,109 --> 01:24:36,340
It was a refreshing trip.

2188
01:24:37,140 --> 01:24:39,909
(And precious people he met in India
that he is thankful for)

2189
01:24:40,210 --> 01:24:43,350
(He could experience the unfamiliar world
more deeply thanks to them.)

2190
01:24:43,880 --> 01:24:46,619
(He made unforgettable memories
by accident.)

2191
01:24:47,350 --> 01:24:48,460
It was fun.

2192
01:24:48,460 --> 01:24:50,020
(After finishing the journey
where he traveled 13,346km in total...)

2193
01:24:51,689 --> 01:24:55,899
Now, I'm going back to Korea
to catch up on things.

2194
01:24:55,899 --> 01:24:57,300
(It's time to go back
to his daily life now.)

2195
01:24:57,529 --> 01:24:59,100
There are so many things to do.

2196
01:25:00,000 --> 01:25:02,600
But I can't wait to work on them.

2197
01:25:03,170 --> 01:25:06,569
I feel grateful for my daily life
after coming to India.

2198
01:25:06,569 --> 01:25:08,710
(He gained energy to return
to his mundane life through this trip.)

2199
01:25:08,710 --> 01:25:10,079
The sun has risen.

2200
01:25:11,140 --> 01:25:12,180
Let's...

2201
01:25:13,310 --> 01:25:16,479
do our best in life.

2202
01:25:16,920 --> 01:25:18,149
Why do we have to do our best?

2203
01:25:18,420 --> 01:25:21,250
Everyone, do what you want in life...

2204
01:25:22,090 --> 01:25:23,189
and die.

2205
01:25:24,819 --> 01:25:26,390
- People all die.
- Yes.

2206
01:25:26,390 --> 01:25:28,260
- You should have no regrets when you die.
- It's to leave no regrets.

2207
01:25:30,899 --> 01:25:32,500
I'll see you again in Korea.

2208
01:25:37,140 --> 01:25:40,170
(The long yet short trip to India ends!)

2209
01:25:54,489 --> 01:25:55,590
- Oh, my.
- Gosh.

2210
01:25:56,260 --> 01:25:58,460
(Adventure by Accident 2)

2211
01:25:58,460 --> 01:25:59,659
It was touching.

2212
01:25:59,760 --> 01:26:02,460
(The second journey is over.)

2213
01:26:02,460 --> 01:26:04,399
(Here's a bonus scene.)

2214
01:26:05,229 --> 01:26:09,100
(Last July,
after finishing the second journey,)

2215
01:26:09,739 --> 01:26:12,710
(Kian84 came to feel the sea.)

2216
01:26:16,510 --> 01:26:18,039
I'm not impressed because I'm old.

2217
01:26:19,250 --> 01:26:20,850
The infrastructure here is too good.

2218
01:26:21,350 --> 01:26:23,880
Trains and cars. So many restaurants.

2219
01:26:24,579 --> 01:26:26,020
What kind of sea do you want to go to?

2220
01:26:26,319 --> 01:26:29,289
The sea people depend on to make a living.

2221
01:26:30,659 --> 01:26:32,359
Where people fish...

2222
01:26:32,989 --> 01:26:34,260
- with harpoons.
- Harpoons.

2223
01:26:34,529 --> 01:26:35,930
A beautiful sea.

2224
01:26:37,460 --> 01:26:39,029
(It suits a manly man in nature.)

2225
01:26:39,029 --> 01:26:40,729
I'm going into the water.

2226
01:26:41,430 --> 01:26:42,470
(Diving)

2227
01:26:42,470 --> 01:26:44,539
Let's go to the sea in season three.

2228
01:26:44,539 --> 01:26:45,609
Let's go.

2229
01:26:46,939 --> 01:26:49,079
(Into the wild)

2230
01:26:50,840 --> 01:26:52,979
(Adventure by Accident will return...)

2231
01:26:52,979 --> 01:26:55,750
(with the primeval sea!)
